:"http://ma.tt/?p=14085";s:4:"link";s:35:"http://ma.tt/2009/04/polldaddy-php/";s:11:"description";s:202:"<p><a href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2009/04/22/polldaddy-just-got-a-new-heart/">PollDaddy just finished their big switch from ASP.NET/SQL to PHP/MySQL</a>. Go and give the guys a virtual Guinness.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 23 Apr 2009 22:28:43 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:4:"Matt";}s:7:"summary";s:202:"<p><a href="http://blog.polldaddy.com/2009/04/22/polldaddy-just-got-a-new-heart/">PollDaddy just finished their big switch from ASP.NET/SQL to PHP/MySQL</a>. Go and give the guys a virtual Guinness.</p>";}i:11;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:45:"BuddyPress: BuddyPress 1.0 RC-2 Now Available";s:4:"guid";s:28:"http://buddypress.org/?p=332";s:4:"link";s:65:"http://buddypress.org/blog/news/buddypress-10-rc-2-now-available/";s:11:"description";s:951:"<p>BuddyPress version 1.0 RC-2 has now been tagged and made available for <a href="http://buddypress.org/download">download</a>.</p>\n<p>This release requires <a href="http://mu.wordpress.org/download/">version 2.7.1 of WordPress MU</a>, but for good reason. It is now possible to automatically download, install and upgrade BuddyPress from within the WordPress MU plugin admin area.</p>\n<p>If you are upgrading from RC-1 it is very important that you read the <a href="http://codex.buddypress.org/getting-started/installing-buddypress/upgrading-from-rc-1/">upgrade instructions</a> as the installation and setup of BuddyPress has changed significantly.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re installing BuddyPress for the first time, please follow the <a href="http://codex.buddypress.org/getting-started/installing-buddypress/">updated installation instructions</a>.</p>\n<p>We are now in the final stretch. Version 1.0 will be available within a week from today.</p>";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Thu, 23 Apr 2009 20:20:39 +0000";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:9:"apeatling";}s:7:"summary";s:951:"<p>BuddyPress version 1.0 RC-2 has now been tagged and made available for <a href="http://buddypress.org/download">download</a>.</p>\n<p>This release requires <a href="http://mu.wordpress.org/download/">version 2.7.1 of WordPress MU</a>, but for good reason. It is now possible to automatically download, install and upgrade BuddyPress from within the WordPress MU plugin admin area.</p>\n<p>If you are upgrading from RC-1 it is very important that you read the <a href="http://codex.buddypress.org/getting-started/installing-buddypress/upgrading-from-rc-1/">upgrade instructions</a> as the installation and setup of BuddyPress has changed significantly.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re installing BuddyPress for the first time, please follow the <a href="http://codex.buddypress.org/getting-started/installing-buddypress/">updated installation instructions</a>.</p>\n<p>We are now in the final stretch. Version 1.0 will be available within a week from today.</p>";}i:12;a:7:{s:5:"title";s:59:"Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Theme Releases for 04/23";s:4:"guid";s:40:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/?p=5684";s:4:"link";s:87:"http://weblogtoolscollection.com/archives/2009/04/23/wordpress-theme-releases-for-0423/";s:11:"description";s:3029:"<p><a href="http://netizensmedia.com/2009/04/20/introducing-undercon-better-sweeter-customizable-wordpress-domain-parking-theme/">Undercon</a></p>\n<p><img title="undercon" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/undercon.gif" alt="undercon" width="200" height="100" /></p>\n<p>UnderCon is a customizable WordPress Domain Parking theme. It includes a theme options page that allows you to customize the title, description and logo. Easy Feedburner integration.</p>\n<p><a href="http://www.ziosteve.com/wptheme-brown/">Yaveo</a></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.temi-wordpress.com/go.php?http://www.temi-wordpress.com/testrun23/index.php?wptheme=Yaveo"><img title="Yaveo" src="http://weblogtoolscollection.com/b2-img/2009/04/yaveo.jpg" alt="Yaveo" width="200" height="150" /></a></p>\n<p>Two column, widget ready, simp